The paper focuses on image restoration using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of denoising-based algorithms and convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are also commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions super-resolution and deblurring, which are sub-topics of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of the denoisers and back-projection modules, which involves information theory (cs.IT).
